snippet.title: Once a refugee, supermodel Alek Wek returns to South Sudan to help others
snippet.description:
* South Sudan, the newest country in the world, is already facing a crisis. With more than 170,000 refugees on its northern border, and hundreds of thousands of people who have returned since independence, the newborn country is struggling.
http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/04/world/iyw-south-sudan-wek/index.html

snippet.title: Supermodel Alek Wek's emotional homecoming
snippet.description:
* South Sudan is in the news but not for the reasons that moved me to fly halfway around the world to the country were I was born. South Sudan, my country, has been criticized for not having done enough since its independence.
http://www.cnn.com/2012/09/11/world/africa/alek-wek-south-sudan-journey/index.html

snippet.title: ELLE
snippet.description:
* Makeup genius, Pat McGraths simple piece of advice to the girls is to cleanse; find a cleanser and carry it everywhere, as religiously as those Marlboros. Runway veterans, such as Kate and Naomi have already taken this to heart, whilst Alek Wek drinks loads of milk, and uses masses of vasoline.
http://www.cnn.com/STYLE/ELLE/9811/06/index.html

snippet.title: ELLE
snippet.description:
* With dozens of new African faces, the National Association of ModelAgents is fighting back and making serious inroads. And the timing couldnt be better. Sudanese model Alek Wek has revolutionized the way the industry looks at black models. Alek is Africa 2000 the bloodline of her broad cheekbone...
